package com.palhelper.app.data

import com.palhelper.app.data.model.Pal

/**
 * Static Palworld 1.0 breeding dataset.
 *
 * Breeding-rank values and the full 297-Pal roster were extracted from palworld.gg's 1.0
 * breeding calculator (July 2026), which exposes each Pal's real breeding-rank number. This
 * replaced the old Early-Access-era table that produced wrong results after the 1.0 patch
 * reshuffled ranks and added ~73 new Pals. Note the 1.0 rank scale runs up to ~3100 (not the
 * old ~1500 ceiling), and LOWER rank = rarer/stronger.
 *
 * The child of two parents is floor((rankA + rankB + 1) / 2), resolved to the formula-eligible
 * Pal with the closest rank (see [com.palhelper.app.domain.BreedingCalculator]).
 *
 * `eligibleAsFormulaChild = false` marks sub-species/variant Pals that can't be produced by the
 * averaging formula; they come only from a fixed pair in [specialCombinations] (or, for a few,
 * same-species breeding in [sameSpeciesOnlyIds]).
 *
 * Icons are hotlinked from palworld.gg and loaded at runtime (see PalIcon); nothing is bundled.
 *
 * The 4th Pal(...) argument is a deterministic tie-break index (list position). Palworld's real
 * tie-break is Paldex file order, which isn't published in this source; genuine equidistant ties
 * are rare, so list order is used as a stable stand-in. If a specific tie-broken result is ever
 * reported wrong, adjust that Pal's index or add a verified override in [specialCombinations].
 */
